    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hey @amit4106udale I can't make any real suggestions here, as I know very little about your stack.\r\nI'll assume you're using InstantSearch.js, in case which what's you want can be accomplished with a [refinementList](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/refinement-list/js/).\r\n\r\nHere are the steps, roughly:\r\n\r\n1. in your Algolia Dashboard, make sure `restaurant` attribute is added as a facet. (see [our docs](https://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/managing-results/refine-results/faceting/how-to/declaring-attributes-for-faceting/) if you don't know how to do this)\r\n\r\n2. add a refinementList widget with attribute `restaurant`, very much like we do it on this example with attribute `brand` in this example: https://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/managing-results/refine-results/faceting/how-to/declaring-attributes-for-faceting/\r\n\r\nI hope this helps. Closing but feel free to reopen if this doesn't answer your question.",
